                <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Relevance</emphasis></entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>10.3.1</entry>
                <entry>Use simple and compound growth formulae.</entry>
                <entry morerows="1">The mathematics of finance is very relevant to daily and long-term financial decisions learners will need to make in terms of investing, taking loans, saving and understanding exchange rates and their influence more globally.</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>10.3.2</entry>
                <entry>Implications of fluctuating exchange rates.</entry>
