              <row>
                <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Outcome</emphasis></entry>
                <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Relevance</emphasis></entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>10.7.1</entry>
                <entry>Investigate, form and try to prove conjectures about properties of special triangles, quadrilaterals and other polygons.Disprove false conjectures using counter-examples.Investigate alternative definitions of various polygons.</entry>
                <entry morerows="1">The thinking processes and mathematical skills of proving conjectures and identifying false conjectures is more the relevance here than the actual content studied. The surface area and volume content studied in real-life contexts of designing kitchens, tiling and painting rooms, designing packages, etc. is relevant to the current and future lives of learners. </entry>
